  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Louisiana totaled $3.6B for FY2026 to date. All figures are contract obligations; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). AwardCount for the period is 18,003, with an AverageAwardSize of $199K. Obligations are down 24.8% year over year. Comparing recent fiscal years shows variability: FY21 was $4B, FY22 was $3.7B, FY23 was $4.5B, FY24 was $3.9B, and FY25 was $4.8B, followed by the FY26 to-date total of $3.6B. The distribution of FY2026 to-date obligations is concentrated in a small number of agencies and industries: the Department of Homeland Security and the Department of Defense account for $1.5B and $1.4B respectively, and Ship Building and Repairing accounts for $1.6B. Vendor concentration is also evident, led by BOLLINGER SHIPYARDS LOCKPORT, L.L.C. at $1.3B and followed by other leading vendors and industries that appear in the FY2026 to-date rankings. These figures describe the current fiscal-year-to-date federal contracting landscape in Louisiana.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How does FY2026 to date compare with prior fiscal years?",
        "body": "FY2026 to date obligations are $3.6B, which follows FY25 at $4.8B and FY24 at $3.9B. Obligations are down 24.8% year over year. Historical annual totals include FY21 at $4B, FY22 at $3.7B, and FY23 at $4.5B, showing multi-year fluctuations. The FY2026 to-date figure is a partial total for the fiscal year."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and industries account for the largest shares of spending?",
        "body": "The top two buying agencies for FY2026 to date are the Department of Homeland Security at $1.5B and the Department of Defense at $1.4B. Industry concentration is led by Ship Building and Repairing at $1.6B and Other Heavy and Civil Engineering Construction at $451M. The Department of Energy records $255M and Facilities Support Services records $385M in FY2026 to-date obligations. Top vendor concentration is high, with BOLLINGER SHIPYARDS LOCKPORT, L.L.C. at $1.3B."
      }
